{
  "texts": [
    "LLMs are resource-hungry models; retraining them is costly and requires a large infrastructure.",
    "Parameter efficient finetuning techniques (PEFT) [24] allows fine-tuning without needing such a large infrastructure.",
    "We leverage Low-Rank Adaptation (LoRA) [25] and QLoRA (INT4) [26] to fine-tune the model on a single Nvidia V100 GPU machine.",
    "The final trained LoRA adapter is merged into the base model in FP16, to be used in inference.Additionally, we will explore zero and fewshot learning to enhance the model's ability to generalize across diverse intent expressions.",
    "Even when fed prompts with near-identical meaning, LLMs can generate wildly different responses [27]."
  ]
}